property.value:
A simple demo for the ScarabGoalPublisher accessor. To run this demo, Scarab must be running ROS and rosbridge. It automatically subscribes to the topic "/goal" for its waypoints. This works with the simulation documented here: https://www.terraswarm.org/accessors/wiki/Main/ InstallingTheScarabsROSPackages#Run
The accessor takes in the following 3 inputs: 1. address (string) of rosbridge, eg: "localhost" or "127.0.0.1" 2. port (number) of rosbridge, eg: 9090 3. pose information if JSON form. The formatting is as follows: { "position": //cartesian coordinates {"x":.., "y":.. "z":..}, "orientation": //quaternion orientation (final orientation of robot) {"w":.., "x":.., "y":.., "z":..} }
In this demo, the position coordinates are provided by the 'values' parameter in DiscreteClock.
To make Scarab cycle between (x=0, y=0) and (x=2.5, y=0) every 5 seconds, configure the DiscreteClock as follows: Period: 10 Offset: {0.0, 5.0} Values:{{position={x=0, y=0, z=0}, orientation={w=1, x=0, y=0, z=0}}, {position={x=2.5, y=0, z=0}, orientation={w=1, x=0, y=0, z=0}}}

